Snapshots of cairo and glitz for mozilla usage.

We only include the relevant parts of each release (generally, src/*.[ch]),
as we have Makefile.in's that integrate into the Mozilla build system.  For
documentation and similar, please see the official tarballs at
http://www.cairographics.org/.

VERSIONS:

  cairo (1.18.4)
  pixman (0.46.4)

==== Local cairo patches ====

00-cairo_public.patch: allow cairo_public to be predefined

01-xlib-xrender-private.patch: xrender build fix

02-cplusplus-no-register.patch: 'register' keyword not allowed when cairo.h is included by C++ code

03-expose-lcd-filter.patch: expose the LCD filter settings as public API

04-subpixel-aa-api.patch: add API for setting subpixel-AA

05-ft-font-synth-flags-api.patch: enable client to control whether FreeType synthetic styles are allowed

06-shared-ft-face.patch: integrate with Gecko SharedFTFace

07-ft-variations-runtime-check.patch: runtime check for FreeType variation support

08-quartz-surface-additions.patch: add cairo_quartz_surface_get_image

09-quartz-surface-tags.patch: support for LINK tags in the quartz-surface backend

10-quartz-named-destination.patch: support for named destinations in quartz-surface

11-quartz-prefer-named-dest-over-uri.patch: prefer named destinations over URI links in quartz-surface

12-active-edges-crash.patch: avoid potential crash in active_edges

13-quartz-granular-ifdefs.patch: build fixes for iOS

14-ft-color-ifdef.patch: guard FT_COLOR_H and related FreeType/fontconfig symbols for builds targeting older FreeType

15-ios-colorspace.patch: iOS doesn't support per-display color spaces

16-quartz-surface-leak.patch: fix DataSourceSurfaceRawData leak on quartz surface

17-windows-build-fix.patch: build fix for Windows/non-mingw

18-win32-api-additions.patch: Windows API additions for gecko

19-quartz-surface-mask.patch: don't apply clip to CGContext for quartz surface mask

20-windows-sdk-26100.patch: fix build bustage with Windows SDK 26100

21-win32-vertical-glyph-advance-direction.patch: fix sign of glyph y-advance for ExtTextOut

22-tor-scan-converter-polygon.patch: protect add_polygon with setjmp to avoid crash on jmp_buf corruption

23-cff-subroutine-offset.patch: add bounds check in cff_index_read to avoid out-of-bounds read

24-cff-fdselect-range-check.patch: add bounds check in cff_fdselect_read to avoid out-of-bounds read

25-quartz-revert-to-pre-1.18.0.patch: revert cairo-quartz-*.[ch] to the pre-1.18.0 Mozilla state (Bug 1901043 + Bug 1908587 + Bug 1970983); applies on top of the Mozilla-local quartz patches (08, 09, 10, 11, 13, 15, 16, 19)

==== pixman patches ====

pixman-armasm.patch: add an ifdef guard around pixman-config.h include

pixman-export.patch: make sure pixman symbols are not exported in libxul

pixman-interp.patch: use lower quality interpolation by default on mobile

pixman-rename.patch: include pixman-rename.h for renaming of external symbols
